shared_text:
Jeanna Zitting
October 15, 2018 at 3:44 PM ·

TOMORROW IS THE DAY. :) Want to give your preschoolers the foundation they need for reading success in kindergarten? Do you have a 1st, 2nd or 3rd grader who is struggling to learn to read? Do you plan on having children in the future and want to know how to build their 'reading brains'? This parent night will help you understand the foundational developmental pieces that must be in place for a child to learn to read AND give you the time and space to practice specific skills and strategies you can use to help your child. This training is led by trained professionals in language and physical development and is your gift from Masada. This night is open to the public, all parents, future parents, siblings, etc are welcome to attend!
Held at Masada Charter School in the Multipurpose room.

The PRISM Committee is requesting parents to come with their children to the luncheons and movie nights.

Today at the luncheon many young children were left unsupervised and were disorderly in the school and on the grounds. The PRISM representatives at these occasions are busy hosting the events and it is unfair of parents to expect them to supervise kids. The PRISM designs these occasions as opportunities for parents and children to enjoy time together. Your support is very much appreciated! We recognize we have amazing parent support in many ways. This is just an area that needs improving. Thank you!

post_text:
Dear Parents,

Due to a need to reschedule professional development for teachers we have shifted the first day of school for Masada from August 19th to August 26th for the 2016-17 school year. Though we are starting a week later than originally planned, we are not adding an entire week to the end of the school year. We have adjusted our calendar so that we can makeup the week by going to school on Labor Day and adding two days on to the end of the year. Therefore school will be out on Friday, May 26, 2017 instead of Wednesday, May 24th. We sincerely hope that you as parents experience no inconvenience due to this shift. And thank you for the support that you continue to give us year after year in building a program that serves you and your students.

With Regards,

Masada Administration

Dear Parents,

In an effort to accomodate funeral services on Tuesday, Masada will be releasing early for the Holiday Break. Today will be our last day of attendance this year. We will be returning to school on Wednesday, January 2, 3013.
There is still time to send stocking stuffers if you would like to participate. Teachers are accepting stocking stuffers until later this afternoon. The stockings will be handed to students at the end of the day today.
We have a large number of sick students. Please do all you can during this Holiday Season to promote health and wellness.

Happy Holidays from all of us!!

Masada

post_text: Masada is looking for a part time School Nurse (RN) to work 1 to 2 days per week with flexible hours. If your are interested stop by the main office and get an application. A resume and 3 letters of reference will be needed and can be emailed to Ms. LeAnne at leannet@masadaschool.com. The position pays $25 per hour and applications must be received by July 20th. School Nurse experience is preferred.
